#: ../../mapping.md:60
#: 484b76061c6c4d488623d2e9344e80d6
msgid "Time series"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:62
#: effd8adfdbe6460a985fc2784e642c25
msgid "With the `timeSeriesName` variable you can map any time series by referring to its name. The available time series  must exist in the input data set or be created within the groovy script. For more details about time series management,  refer to the [time series description](inv:powsyblcore:*:*#timeseries)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:66
#: a39c4b52fac54ee2991525126c34461f
msgid "Note that if the same time series (referred by its name) is used in multiple `mapToXXX` of same type, the mapping  behavior will be as if it was applied once on the group of elements selected by these `mapToXXX` instructions.  For instance, if we map a constant time series of value 100, to a generator A and in another mapTo, to a generator B,  then, with the default distributionKey, it will map the value 50 to each generator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:71
#: 8beddbe06acb40179a606c8378dfebc5
msgid "Variable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:73
#: f5d6e203cabb4cac993e26b1bfe6105f
msgid "The `variable` allows to specify which network element attribute will be overwritten by its mapped time series value. It is an optional variable (except for `mapToTransformers`) which values depends on the element type (default is in bold) :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:76
#: c8a76aa220754822957e74cb1db33292
msgid "`mapToGenerators` **targetP**, minP, maxP, targetQ"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:77
#: c9234759fd7947c5b032429a15e0fe83
msgid "`mapToLoads` **p0**, fixedActivePower, variableActivePower, q0, fixedReactivePower, variableReactivePower"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:78
#: 681131480e13408aa0b359112b00ba60
msgid "`mapToHvdcLines` **activePowerSetpoint**, minP, maxP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:79
#: 9d3c719e9dd94f24b9149b2e2b5e3b91
msgid "`mapToBoundaryLines` **p0**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:80
#: dabb6604d61e40b69da5a78f9df4fcbb
msgid "`mapToBreakers` **open** (with 1 corresponding to a closed switch and 0 to open)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:81
#: b99a04a54d2f4ee7aae15eaeb36b2ebf
msgid "`mapToTransformers` ratedU1, ratedU2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:82
#: da4188b4c17e472ca102cebb411270af
msgid "`mapToPhaseTapChangers` **phaseTapPosition**, phaseRegulating (0: off, 1: on), regulationMode (0: CURRENT_LIMITER, 1: ACTIVE_POWER_CONTROL, 2: FIXED_TAP)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:83
#: 2536d79ac20543b898d940a208b1dc4b
msgid "`mapToRatioTapChangers` **ratioTapPosition**, loadTapChangingCapabilities, regulating, targetV"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:84
#: 3b78098788ed4e7eab8001169f7530f1
msgid "`mapToLccConverterStations` **powerFactor**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:85
#: 9a1513948fc04e7a83f6037c8eed0d7d
msgid "`mapToVscConverterStations` **voltageSetpoint**, voltageRegulatorOn, reactivePowerSetpoint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:87
#: 14665f5ad13a4c0683dac3ffa911d806
msgid "For the loads, it is forbidden to map `p0` and in the same time `fixedActivePower` or `variableActivePower`, as these variables are linked (`p0 = Pfixed + Pvar`). It is restricted to prevent incoherent mapping. If only `fixedActivePower` or `variableActivePower` is mapped, then the value of the other unmapped one will be set to 0 by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:89
#: 4447b7f1b31b493eb9be7a63b0e96e3f
msgid "Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:91
#: 12b5615a79844e20aa0533fbeb98cb2d
msgid "The `filter` variable is evaluated for every network item (of the requested type) and only those which match will be mapped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:93
#: 4744859410db4389b2edad9956efbdac
msgid "The filter must be a groovy statement returning `true` or `false`. It has access to the same variables of the main script, with three more variables related to the current object filtered."
msgstr ""

