#: ../../mapping.md:281
#: a8445fbc23f44e149f61cc4b6ce3165d
msgid "The use of the option `--mapping-synthesis-dir` produces csv synthesis files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:283
#: ddc707b835974d1aa766e290dac9a75f
msgid "The file `mappingSynthesis.csv/txt` contains a csv/text formatted (also displayed in the command line output) global synthesis indicating how the different types of network elements or variables were processed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:284
#: 7f69d256c1a74a529d6924bcf5692f45
msgid "mapped: elements that were mapped with time series"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:285
#: 7f378892caa54f01afba87ad786bd6c2
msgid "unmapped: elements that weren't mapped at all"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:286
#: 1b0bfb3421d9445f8098e73fe01ab814
msgid "ignored unmapped: elements that weren't mapped but specifically indicated so"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:287
#: db9ef905e26b490fbc719cd7d5ecf643
msgid "multi-mapped: elements that were mapped multiple times (often when we map all elements of one type once then we apply another with a specific filter), only the last mapping will be applied"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:288
#: c12abb86639a4945b28a99c33513f589
msgid "disconnected: number of disconnected elements (as mapping do not apply to them)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:289
#: 87218af6884543e7a4c59ec967d0a5c2
msgid "out of main cc: number of elements that are out of the main connected component (as mapping do not apply to them)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:291
#: 9ffa362c8aa1418eaefa17c6d94d88db
msgid "Component type represents the network element (generators, loads, breakers, etc.):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:292
#: 8907c74be3044ff0bbcea22daa013cf8
msgid "Files with template name `<componentType>ToTimeSeriesMapping.csv` show the effective mapping between time series and the element."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:293
#: 03947f91a5c848a9bd197bfbc19483a6
msgid "Files with template name `disconnected<componentType>.csv` list the disconnected elements with additional information. Note that the time series indicated as \"AppliedTimeSeries\" isn't effectively applied."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:294
#: f76cdf9a488d4ca4b374405ee5e4fadd
msgid "Same or similar information can be found for elements that are out of main connected components, unmapped and ignored unmapped, in files with respective template name `outOfMainCc<componentType>.csv`, `unmapped<componentType>.csv` and `ignoredUnmapped<componentType>.csv`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:295
#: 1b36074e9bfa441ab7ebf5d4c687fb5d
msgid "Files with template name `timeSeriesTo<componentType>Mapping` show for each time series how it was used in the mapping, with the original network value and variable type. The file `timeSeries.csv` show the same mapping for all component types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:297
#: c7af2f77f0c74d388b08ca9461659f7f
msgid "When combining with the option `--check-equipment-time-series` (and the required associated option `--check-versions`), two new files are produced:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:298
#: 03f77068531742acbde3f5e29aa970fb
msgid "`balanceSummary.csv` which contains the overall power balance at each time step"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:299
#: 3bf43535206246269d9d87ddfb22caca
msgid "`mapping-logs.csv` which contains information and warnings about the mapping process (for instance Pmin/Pmax violations)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:301
#: 54db2f3c24b340a6aa42b4b6389b2df9
msgid "Mapping status file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:303
#: 6eef0088b17b43b0a9bfc37dd4c42f24
msgid "The use of the option `--mapping-status-file` produces a file which indicates for each available time series if it was used for the mapping."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:305
#: 98eb27bb201f4870a8d1a1724ad6375f
msgid "Time series mapping generation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:307
#: 813d80a53ff94e76b3751f846d034040
msgid "The use of the option `--equipment-time-series-dir` (with required associated options `--check-equipment-time-series` and `--check-versions`) produces a csv with template name `version_<version_number>.csv` containing for each time step the associated value for each component/variable mapped couple."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:309
#: 1c07a775db1c4907a66acdc0b74c1008
msgid "Network variant generation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mapping.md:311
#: 97172a72237248449513ecc01d0381aa
msgid "The use of the option `--network-output-dir`  (with required associated options `--check-equipment-time-series` and `--check-versions`) produces as many IIDM network files as time steps we have in the input time series (with filtering by `--check-versions`, `--first-variant` and `--max-variant-count` options). Each produced file has the template name `<network_id>_<version>_<YYYYMMDD>_<HHmm>.xiidm` and is the network generated with values mapped at indicated time step."
msgstr ""
